<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About - To-Do List</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
  <style>
    .about-content {
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 50px auto;
      padding: 40px;
      background: white;
      border-radius: 12px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    }

    .about-content h1 {
      color: #A683E3;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .about-content h2 {
      color: #333;
      margin-top: 30px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
    }

    .about-content p {
      color: #666;
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }

    .about-content ul {
      margin-left: 20px;
      color: #666;
      line-height: 1.8;
    }

    .about-content li {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .back-link {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 30px;
      padding: 12px 24px;
      background: #A683E3;
      color: white;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-radius: 6px;
      transition: all 0.2s;
    }

    .back-link:hover {
      background: #8B6FB8;
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-content">
      <h1>About To-Do List App</h1>
      
      <p>
        A simple, elegant to-do list application to help you stay organized 
        and productive. Built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB.
      </p>

      <h2>Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>✓ Create and manage multiple task lists</li>
        <li>✓ Mark tasks as complete/incomplete</li>
        <li>✓ Edit existing tasks</li>
        <li>✓ Delete tasks you no longer need</li>
        <li>✓ Track your progress with visual statistics</li>
        <li>✓ Responsive design for all devices</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to Use</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Create a custom list:</strong> Simply navigate to 
        <code>/your-list-name</code> in the URL (e.g., /Work, /Shopping).
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Add tasks:</strong> Type your task in the input field and 
        click the + button.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Complete tasks:</strong> Check the checkbox next to any task 
        to mark it as complete.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Edit tasks:</strong> Click the edit icon (✎) to modify a task.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Delete tasks:</strong> Click the × button to remove a task.
      </p>

      <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to To-Do List</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer>
    <p>© <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> To-Do List App</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>